<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-05T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-05T22:00:00-05:00" n="974" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d974">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894.52/54: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-06T12:00:00+09:00">March 6,
                                1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 6—12:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>80. Department’s 40, March 5, 11 a.m. Perpetual leaseholds. Draft
                            documents submitted to Foreign Office this morning. Foreign Office
                            perceives no objection to immediate publicity release in Washington.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>